709
01:14:31,080 --> 01:14:34,607
Hurry! Eddie!

710
01:14:37,086 --> 01:14:39,077
Eddie?

711
01:14:44,226 --> 01:14:47,684
[ Gasping, Screaming ]

712
01:14:52,201 --> 01:14:54,328
Eddie, no.

713
01:14:56,906 --> 01:15:02,105
[ Grunting, Gasping ]
Tina! Tina! Help me!

714
01:15:11,587 --> 01:15:16,456
Oh, Mommy.

715
01:15:16,525 --> 01:15:20,188
Please, make it go away.

716
01:15:21,697 --> 01:15:23,824
Make it go away.

717
01:15:23,899 --> 01:15:29,098
Make it go away.

718
01:15:30,039 --> 01:15:34,100
[ Siren Wailing ]

719
01:15:38,647 --> 01:15:41,138
Honey, it's not
your job anymore.

720
01:15:41,217 --> 01:15:43,014
I know. I just
want to take a look.

721
01:15:44,520 --> 01:15:47,683
[ Siren Wailing ]

722
01:15:51,493 --> 01:15:53,688
[ Honking ]

723
01:15:53,762 --> 01:15:57,198
Come on. Get outta there.
Come on!

724
01:16:01,871 --> 01:16:03,805
[ Honking ]

725
01:16:03,873 --> 01:16:07,775
[ Honking ]

726
01:16:07,843 --> 01:16:11,779
[ Honking ]

727
01:16:28,330 --> 01:16:32,323
What happened to him?
Embolism.
Air bubbles in the blood.

728
01:16:32,401 --> 01:16:34,961
[ Man ]
He came up too fast, Chief.
He held his damn breath.

729
01:16:35,037 --> 01:16:39,406
Something must have
scared him down there.
He just panicked.

730
01:16:39,475 --> 01:16:43,206
Don't worry, we're takin'
good care of him. Come on.

731
01:16:43,279 --> 01:16:47,147
Easy!

732
01:16:48,751 --> 01:16:50,685
How did this happen?

733
01:16:50,753 --> 01:16:53,620
[ Hendricks ]
Bite reflex, like a spasm.

734
01:16:53,689 --> 01:16:55,953
Happened about an hour ago,
right after the kids went out.

735
01:16:56,025 --> 01:16:59,654
What kids?
Oh, Junior Vaughn,

736
01:16:59,728 --> 01:17:01,992
Brooke Peters,
Jackie, Mike--

737
01:17:02,064 --> 01:17:03,691
Our Mike?

738
01:17:03,766 --> 01:17:06,360
Yeah, they said they were
headed for the lighthouse.
Hey! Where you goin'?

739
01:17:17,579 --> 01:17:19,513
Look, Chief!

740
01:17:19,581 --> 01:17:22,516
You're not chief anymore.
I can't let you take her out.

741
01:17:22,584 --> 01:17:24,882
Mrs. Brody, look, if he
can't go, then you can't go.

742
01:17:24,954 --> 01:17:26,922
Neither one of you can go.
Chief, please!
Ellen, get that line.

743
01:17:26,989 --> 01:17:30,288
- Mike is out there!
- But I signed for the boat!

744
01:17:30,359 --> 01:17:33,260
Mrs. Brody, please!
Aww, shit!
[ Engine Sputtering ]

745
01:17:33,329 --> 01:17:36,492
Chief, go on up to the bow.
You're doing that wrong.

746
01:17:36,565 --> 01:17:38,499
Go ahead,
untie the bowline.

747
01:17:38,567 --> 01:17:40,728
What the hell? They can't
fire both of us, right?

748
01:17:40,803 --> 01:17:43,499
Somebody's
got to be in charge.

749
01:17:43,572 --> 01:17:46,370
[ Engine Starting ]
All right, which direction
you want to go?

750
01:17:46,442 --> 01:17:48,376
You said something
about a lighthouse!

751
01:17:48,444 --> 01:17:50,378
Let's go!
All right!

752
01:17:56,652 --> 01:18:01,385
[ Honking ]

753
01:18:04,727 --> 01:18:08,720
[ Honking ]

754
01:18:08,797 --> 01:18:11,163
[ Brody ]
Amity Launch to Harbor Patrol.
Over.

755
01:18:11,233 --> 01:18:14,669
[ Man On Radio ]
This is Harbor Patrol.
Yeah, listen, Ed.

756
01:18:14,737 --> 01:18:18,332
Do you think you can
raise me a chopper?
Is that you, Brody?

757
01:18:18,407 --> 01:18:21,342
Not right away.
He's down checking a buoy
in the channel.

758
01:18:21,410 --> 01:18:25,312
I want you to get the chopper
out to the lighthouse.
There's kids day sailing there.

759
01:18:25,381 --> 01:18:27,406
I want them
brought back to port.

760
01:18:27,483 --> 01:18:31,317
Affirmative, turn the kids
day sailing back to port.

761
01:18:31,387 --> 01:18:34,151
I heard ya.
Patrol out.

762
01:18:34,223 --> 01:18:37,522
Brody out.

763
01:18:41,830 --> 01:18:44,128
[ Andy ]
Hurry up, suckers,
you're draggin'.

764
01:18:44,199 --> 01:18:46,827
Yeah, come on.
We're gonna lose ya.

765
01:18:46,902 --> 01:18:50,668
Get that piece of junk
out of the way, huh?

766
01:18:54,176 --> 01:18:57,373
Hey, let's go past
the lighthouse.

767
01:18:57,446 --> 01:18:59,880
[ Mike ]
I know a better spot.
Come about!

768
01:18:59,948 --> 01:19:01,939
You got it!

769
01:19:16,131 --> 01:19:20,727
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

770
01:19:25,641 --> 01:19:30,442
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

771
01:19:39,421 --> 01:19:43,050
[ Indistinct Chatter ]

772
01:20:36,278 --> 01:20:38,269
I got it, Chief.

773
01:20:50,192 --> 01:20:54,458
[ Tina Sobbing ]

774
01:20:57,566 --> 01:21:02,265
[ Sobbing ]

775
01:21:04,373 --> 01:21:07,934
It's all right.
Come on. Come on.

776
01:21:08,010 --> 01:21:10,535
It's okay.
[ Sobbing ]

777
01:21:10,612 --> 01:21:12,546
It's all right.
It's all right.
[ Sobbing ]

778
01:21:12,614 --> 01:21:16,983
Nooo!
Take it easy.
You're all right.

779
01:21:17,052 --> 01:21:19,520
You're all right.
Ellen.

780
01:21:19,588 --> 01:21:22,648
[ Tina ]
No, no, no.

781
01:21:22,724 --> 01:21:24,783
It's all right.
It's all right.

782
01:21:24,860 --> 01:21:29,456
Tina, oh, Tina.
[ Gasping ]
It's still there.

783
01:21:29,531 --> 01:21:32,295
Tina, Tina,
it's okay.
It's still there.

784
01:21:32,367 --> 01:21:34,335
What's the matter?
What's still there?

785
01:21:34,403 --> 01:21:37,463
What's still there?
[ Gasping ]

786
01:21:37,539 --> 01:21:39,734
Sh-sh-sh-sh-sh-shark!

787
01:21:39,808 --> 01:21:42,834
It's still there.
Over there.

788
01:21:42,911 --> 01:21:47,109
[ Sobbing ]

789
01:21:53,488 --> 01:21:56,321
[ Tina Sobbing ]

790
01:21:58,627 --> 01:22:02,996
[ Honking ]

791
01:22:08,904 --> 01:22:12,203
That boat's
gonna take you in.
Where the hell are they?

792
01:22:12,274 --> 01:22:14,242
About ten degrees
off your starboard bow.

793
01:22:14,309 --> 01:22:16,937
Take a heading leeward
of Sand Island--
Don't give me that shit, point!

794
01:22:17,012 --> 01:22:19,242
- There!
- All right, I got it.

795
01:22:22,117 --> 01:22:24,108
[ Engine Starting ]

796
01:22:38,634 --> 01:22:41,933
[ Doug ]
Mr. Christian,
Mr. Christian.

797
01:22:42,004 --> 01:22:46,202
Pump up this boat. Shave off
that dreadful moustache.

798
01:22:46,275 --> 01:22:50,905
England expects every man
to do his duty. You may
fire when ready, Quigley.

799
01:22:50,979 --> 01:22:54,073
Damn the torpedoes!
Full speed ahead.

800
01:22:54,149 --> 01:22:57,414
This will be
our finest hour!

801
01:22:58,553 --> 01:23:01,522
Oh, shit.

802
01:23:01,590 --> 01:23:04,354
[ Laughing ]
Hey, Bligh, someone
pop your balloon?

803
01:23:04,426 --> 01:23:06,951
It's no problem.
No problem.

804
01:23:09,097 --> 01:23:12,191
[ Doug Indistinct ]

805
01:23:12,267 --> 01:23:15,168
[ Group Screaming ]

806
01:23:19,441 --> 01:23:21,602
[ Group Yelling ]

807
01:23:23,578 --> 01:23:25,205
[ Group Yelling ]

808
01:23:26,581 --> 01:23:28,811
Come on!

809
01:23:31,086 --> 01:23:34,647
[ Screaming ]

810
01:23:35,824 --> 01:23:38,816
[ Mike ]
Balance the boat.

811
01:23:52,107 --> 01:23:54,735
All right! All right!
It's all right!

812
01:23:54,810 --> 01:23:56,937
Watch it!
Marge!

813
01:23:59,815 --> 01:24:01,544
Kevin, do something!

814
01:24:02,651 --> 01:24:05,677
Sean!

815
01:24:05,754 --> 01:24:07,619
Oh, no!

816
01:24:07,689 --> 01:24:10,249
Timmy! Brooke!

817
01:24:10,325 --> 01:24:12,759
Hey, you guys!

818
01:24:12,828 --> 01:24:15,695
Timmy! Swim!

819
01:24:15,764 --> 01:24:17,664
Where is it?
I don't know!

820
01:24:17,733 --> 01:24:20,759
Larry, get me outta here!
I'm gonna get you outta here!
Don't worry!

821
01:24:22,104 --> 01:24:25,767
Larry! Turn!
Turn!

822
01:24:25,841 --> 01:24:30,244
[ Yelling ]

823
01:24:30,312 --> 01:24:32,246
Goddamn!
Shit!

824
01:24:32,314 --> 01:24:35,215
It's okay.

825
01:24:37,319 --> 01:24:39,879
Get outta the water.
Will you hurry up?
Mike's out there!

826
01:24:39,955 --> 01:24:43,447
Hurry up!
Out of the water!

827
01:24:46,895 --> 01:24:51,127
Somebody,
look out for Mike!

828
01:24:51,199 --> 01:24:53,793
Hang on to something!

829
01:24:53,869 --> 01:24:56,269
Mike!
Get outta there!

830
01:24:56,338 --> 01:24:58,329
Hold on!

831
01:24:58,407 --> 01:25:02,275
[ Screaming ]

832
01:25:02,344 --> 01:25:03,902
Oh, my God!

833
01:25:03,979 --> 01:25:06,777
Mike! Mike!

834
01:25:06,848 --> 01:25:09,043
Brody!

835
01:25:09,117 --> 01:25:10,414
Come on.
That's it.

836
01:25:10,485 --> 01:25:14,945
Okay! Get his arms!
Come on!

837
01:25:17,125 --> 01:25:20,925
Get ahold of his jacket!
Get his jacket!

838
01:25:20,996 --> 01:25:23,863
Get him clear.
It's coming up!

839
01:25:23,932 --> 01:25:26,867
Get him up!
Get his leg!

840
01:25:26,935 --> 01:25:29,199
Timmy!
Go! Get him up!

841
01:25:29,271 --> 01:25:32,798
[ Timmy ]
Come on! Come on!
Hold him!

842
01:26:10,479 --> 01:26:12,640
He's bleeding
pretty bad.

843
01:26:15,217 --> 01:26:18,311
We gotta get Mike
to a doctor!

844
01:26:18,386 --> 01:26:21,753
- Can you sail?
- Yeah, we'll take him in.

845
01:26:21,823 --> 01:26:23,723
Go for it, and get some
help out here fast!

846
01:26:23,792 --> 01:26:27,023
Let's go!

847
01:26:41,076 --> 01:26:43,544
Okay, let's raft
this mess up.

848
01:26:46,948 --> 01:26:49,678
Throw this--
Throw it to Brooke.
Brooke!

849
01:26:49,751 --> 01:26:52,481
Get this and
throw it to Marge!

850
01:26:55,223 --> 01:26:56,918
Marge, here!
Take it!

851
01:26:56,992 --> 01:26:59,984
Tie a bowline
around your mast.

852
01:27:00,061 --> 01:27:02,757
Wrap it around.

853
01:27:02,831 --> 01:27:06,130
Easy.
Let me help you.

854
01:27:06,201 --> 01:27:08,761
I don't know
if it's gonna hold.

855
01:27:08,837 --> 01:27:10,998
All right,
somebody put a fender up.

856
01:27:11,072 --> 01:27:14,508
We could use
another hand on this.

857
01:27:14,576 --> 01:27:17,511
Take it easy. Just pull.
Tie it on. All right.

858
01:27:51,446 --> 01:27:53,937
Amity Launch
to Air Patrol One.

859
01:27:54,015 --> 01:27:58,145
Amity Launch
to Air Patrol One.
Do you read me?

860
01:27:58,219 --> 01:28:00,949
[ Man On Radio ]
This is Air Patrol.
Is that you, Brody?

861
01:28:01,022 --> 01:28:03,616
Yeah, listen, do you
have a fix on those kids yet?

862
01:28:03,692 --> 01:28:06,320
Negative,
I'm still down.

863
01:28:06,394 --> 01:28:09,454
You better get the hell up
because I'm out here all alone.

864
01:28:09,531 --> 01:28:13,934
Brody, I gotta switch frequencies.
Call my boss. I'll meet you over
by Francis Shoal.

865
01:28:14,002 --> 01:28:16,869
Harbor Air out.

866
01:28:16,938 --> 01:28:21,272
Francis Shoal? Where
the hell is Francis Shoal?
[ Radio Whining ]

867
01:28:33,755 --> 01:28:36,417
Shit.

868
01:28:36,491 --> 01:28:39,688
I'm all alone out here.

869
01:29:19,634 --> 01:29:21,829
Anybody want
to play charades?

870
01:29:22,904 --> 01:29:25,168
No.

871
01:29:25,240 --> 01:29:29,540
Listen, all we have to do
is land at Cable Junction
and wait.

872
01:29:29,611 --> 01:29:32,045
Yeah, and how are we
gonna do that floating
on this garbage?

873
01:29:35,150 --> 01:29:38,745
What's after Cable Junction?
[ Larry Jr. ]
The Atlantic.

874
01:29:38,820 --> 01:29:41,789
Then Ireland.

875
01:29:44,459 --> 01:29:46,654
God, I'm hungry.

876
01:30:17,125 --> 01:30:19,059
[ Pilot ]
Air Patrol to base.

877
01:30:19,127 --> 01:30:22,824
I have a positive location
on that sailing party.

878
01:30:22,897 --> 01:30:28,631
Disabled and adrift.
About three quarters of
a mile west of Cable Junction.

879
01:30:28,703 --> 01:30:31,536
Wind and tide carrying
them about due east.

880
01:30:31,606 --> 01:30:35,702
[ Cheering ]

881
01:30:36,778 --> 01:30:40,179
[ Cheering ]

882
01:30:40,248 --> 01:30:44,844
[ Cheering ]

883
01:30:54,028 --> 01:30:57,691
[ Muffled Cheering,
Helicopter Rotors Whirring ]

884
01:31:05,507 --> 01:31:07,771
[ Cheering ]

885
01:31:18,686 --> 01:31:21,382
Is everybody all right?
Is anybody hurt?

886
01:31:21,456 --> 01:31:23,048
[ Yelling ]

887
01:31:23,124 --> 01:31:25,490
Now, listen, I'm gonna give you
a tow to Cable Junction.

888
01:31:25,560 --> 01:31:27,960
Then I'm gonna call
the Coast Guard
to send a cutter.

889
01:31:28,029 --> 01:31:31,556
[ Cheering ]
Throw me a line.

890
01:31:31,633 --> 01:31:34,796
Take it easy.
Here we go. All right.

891
01:31:34,869 --> 01:31:37,429
Oh, what a day.
Here you go!

892
01:31:38,506 --> 01:31:41,566
[ Cheering ]

893
01:31:47,315 --> 01:31:48,646
Okay!

894
01:31:50,151 --> 01:31:52,119
Now hold on
to something.

895
01:31:52,187 --> 01:31:53,449
Okay.
Just hurry up!

896
01:31:53,521 --> 01:31:57,321
Better hang on.

897
01:32:40,635 --> 01:32:43,331
[ Screaming ]

898
01:32:44,873 --> 01:32:46,636
[ Screaming ]

899
01:33:15,136 --> 01:33:19,095
[ Screaming ]

900
01:33:25,947 --> 01:33:28,415
[ Screaming ]

901
01:33:56,477 --> 01:33:58,069
- Bob!
- Marge!

902
01:33:58,146 --> 01:33:59,613
Sean!
Oooooh!

903
01:33:59,681 --> 01:34:04,448
- Sean!
- Sean!

904
01:34:04,519 --> 01:34:06,851
Sean! Sean!

905
01:34:06,921 --> 01:34:09,412
Get him up
on the boat!

906
01:34:11,025 --> 01:34:14,017
Sean!
Come on!

907
01:34:14,095 --> 01:34:17,189
Hurry!
Get him up on the boat!

908
01:34:19,467 --> 01:34:23,233
Come on! Come on!

909
01:34:26,274 --> 01:34:28,242
Will you pull me?
I can't get up!

910
01:34:28,309 --> 01:34:32,541
[ Marge Screaming ]

911
01:34:32,613 --> 01:34:36,105
Nooooo!

912
01:34:36,184 --> 01:34:40,450
[ Screaming ]

913
01:34:43,458 --> 01:34:46,859
Take her to the hospital.
Meet me back at the office
on the double.

914
01:34:50,465 --> 01:34:52,899
[ Len ]
You gotta try to
understand my position.

915
01:34:52,967 --> 01:34:56,960
Tina's gonna be all right.
Are you okay?

916
01:34:57,038 --> 01:34:59,836
Ellen, I'm sorry.
Believe me, I'm sorry.

917
01:34:59,907 --> 01:35:03,638
I was only thinking of
everyone's interest--
I don't give a damn.

918
01:35:03,711 --> 01:35:07,875
All I know is a boy
is dead and my son and
husband are still out there.

919
01:35:55,363 --> 01:35:58,230
Amity Launch to Harbor Patrol.
Amity Launch to Harbor Patrol.

920
01:35:58,299 --> 01:36:02,292
[ Radio Whining ]

921
01:36:04,639 --> 01:36:07,437
Amity Launch to Harb--
[ Radio Whining ]

922
01:36:07,508 --> 01:36:11,308
Damn!
Damn it!

923
01:36:11,379 --> 01:36:15,679
[ Thunderclap ]

924
01:36:16,951 --> 01:36:18,816
Sean, catch the rope!

925
01:36:18,886 --> 01:36:22,344
Sean, goddamn it!
Sean!

926
01:36:22,423 --> 01:36:24,391
Try and
catch the rope!

927
01:36:24,459 --> 01:36:28,862
Sean! The rope!
Come on, Sean!

928
01:36:30,431 --> 01:36:32,763
Come on, kid!

929
01:36:32,834 --> 01:36:36,201
Sean! Catch the rope!
The rope, Sean!
Come on!

930
01:36:36,270 --> 01:36:38,238
Come on, Sean!

931
01:36:38,306 --> 01:36:41,434
Come on. He's got to help,
or it's not going to work.

932
01:36:41,509 --> 01:36:44,171
Will you stop!
Come on, Sean!
Wake up!

933
01:36:44,245 --> 01:36:46,577
Look at us!

934
01:36:49,750 --> 01:36:51,741
Sean!

935
01:36:51,819 --> 01:36:55,050
Sean, goddamn it!
Goddamn it, Sean!

936
01:36:55,123 --> 01:36:57,648
You listen to me,
or I'll break your ass,
do you hear?

937
01:37:00,461 --> 01:37:02,395
[ Larry Jr. ]
Okay, come on!
Come on!

938
01:37:02,463 --> 01:37:05,023
[ Andy ]
Okay, okay,
Sean, listen.

939
01:37:05,099 --> 01:37:07,863
Listen, we're gonna throw
you this rope, and you
damn well better catch it!

940
01:37:07,935 --> 01:37:11,268
Okay, Sean,
you ready?

941
01:37:11,339 --> 01:37:13,933
Here it comes, kid!

942
01:37:17,678 --> 01:37:19,578
Get it, Sean!

943
01:37:19,647 --> 01:37:21,877
Sean, get it!

944
01:37:21,949 --> 01:37:24,213
Sean, come it!
Get it!

945
01:37:25,520 --> 01:37:27,818
Okay, good.
Tie it around the centerboard.

946
01:37:27,889 --> 01:37:30,790
Tie it tight!

947
01:37:32,326 --> 01:37:35,295
Okay, you ready?
Hold on!

948
01:37:35,363 --> 01:37:39,959
Hang on, okay?
Here we go!
Hold on tight.

949
01:37:45,206 --> 01:37:48,403
Come on.

950
01:37:49,610 --> 01:37:53,376
Okay, kid?

951
01:37:53,447 --> 01:37:57,247
Take it easy.

952
01:37:57,318 --> 01:38:00,446
Come on. Okay!

953
01:38:00,521 --> 01:38:05,458
- Oh, my God!
-Jesus! Get him out!

954
01:38:05,526 --> 01:38:09,758
- Come on, come on!
- Get him on the boat!

955
01:38:16,837 --> 01:38:19,670
Oh, God!
Are you okay, kid?

956
01:38:19,740 --> 01:38:22,231
I thought we lost you.
It's all right. I got you.

957
01:38:28,816 --> 01:38:31,580
Cable Junction's ahead.

958
01:38:31,652 --> 01:38:33,882
Can we make it?
I don't know!

959
01:38:33,955 --> 01:38:37,447
Hey, I was just asking.
I don't know.

960
01:38:39,460 --> 01:38:41,690
How's she doing?

961
01:38:41,762 --> 01:38:44,731
Just gotta
keep her warm.

962
01:38:46,934 --> 01:38:48,925
Somebody give me a hand.
We might be able to steer
this thing.

963
01:38:50,404 --> 01:38:52,395
